           SHORT="Anthy is a Kanji conversion system for Japanese input methods."
cat << EOF
Anthy is a Kanji conversion system for Japanese input methods. It converts
Hiragana text to Kana/Kanji mixed text. Anthy includes grammar definition files
and library files which determine the conversions made. With Anthy and an input
method such as scim or kinput you can type Hiragana (phonetic script) and have
it automatically converted to Kanji (ideographic script).
EOF
